## Progressive tutorials build understanding layer by layer

**[shareAI-lab/claw0](https://github.com/shareAI-lab/claw0)** — Python, Anthropic Claude

Build a complete agent framework **section by section** across 10 incremental steps and roughly 7,000 total lines. Section 1 (`s01_agent_loop.py`) is a bare `while True` + `stop_reason` check. Section 2 adds a tool dispatch table. Subsequent sections add sessions, persistence, WebSocket gateways, heartbeats, and concurrency — each introducing exactly **one new concept** while keeping all prior code intact. Available in English, Chinese, and Japanese. Dependencies are minimal: just `anthropic`, `python-dotenv`, `websockets`, `httpx`.

**[pguso/ai-agents-from-scratch](https://github.com/pguso/ai-agents-from-scratch)** — JavaScript, local LLMs via node-llama-cpp

A structured curriculum rebuilding LangChain's core abstractions from scratch in JavaScript. Eight progressive examples move from basic LLM calls through translation, batch processing, and coding to simple agents, memory agents, and full **ReAct agents**. Each lesson includes both `CODE.md` and `CONCEPT.md`. Uses **local LLMs only** (no API keys needed), making it zero-cost to learn. The explicit formula: `AI Agent = LLM + System Prompt + Tools + Memory + Reasoning Pattern`.

**[disler/MinimalChainable](https://gist.github.com/disler/d51d7e37c3e5f8d277d8e0a71f4a1d2e)** — Python, any LLM (Anthropic Claude examples)

A single GitHub Gist implementing prompt chaining in approximately **50 lines of core code**. The `MinimalChainable` class chains sequential prompts where each can reference prior outputs via `{output[-1]}` syntax. The companion `FusionChain` runs the same chain across multiple models simultaneously and ranks results. Zero library dependencies. Explicitly positioned as "ditching LangChain," this is the **purest possible implementation of prompt chaining** — the pattern that most "workflow" frameworks wrap in hundreds of lines of abstraction.

