## Conclusion

The core insight across all 14 repos is that **agentic AI reduces to a remarkably small set of primitives**. The canonical tool-use agent is 50–100 lines: define functions with JSON schemas, send them with your prompt, parse the model's tool calls, execute locally, append results, loop. Multi-agent coordination adds one more concept — handoffs or message passing. Prompt chaining is string interpolation in a for loop. The repos from Anthropic (`anthropic-cookbook/patterns/agents/`) and OpenAI (`swarm`, `openai-cookbook/Orchestrating_agents.ipynb`) deserve first attention because they're authoritative and framework-free by design. For the deepest understanding, pair them with mini-swe-agent (proving 100 lines can match production systems) and PocketFlow (proving 100 lines can be an entire framework). The frameworks aren't hiding complexity — they're wrapping simplicity.